Missing Values

a <- c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, NA, NA)
b <- c(1:7)

df <- data.frame(a, b)


## Missing value
which(is.na(df$a))
## [1] 6 7
table(is.na(df$a))
## 
## FALSE  TRUE 
##     5     2

Replace NA with 0

is.na(df) 
##          a     b
## [1,] FALSE FALSE
## [2,] FALSE FALSE
## [3,] FALSE FALSE
## [4,] FALSE FALSE
## [5,] FALSE FALSE
## [6,]  TRUE FALSE
## [7,]  TRUE FALSE
df[is.na(df)] <- 0

df

Covid 19 Global

# load library
library(readr)

# read csv data
raw_covid19_confirmed <- read_csv("https://bit.ly/covid19_confirmed")
raw_covid19_deaths <- read_csv("http://bit.ly/covid19_deaths")
raw_covid19_recovered <- read_csv("https://bit.ly/covid19_recover")

# display data
raw_covid19_confirmed
# library load 
library(tidyr)
library(lubridate)


# pivoting in longer format
confirmed <- raw_covid19_confirmed %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = 5:ncol(raw_covid19_confirmed),
               names_to = "date" , 
               values_to = "confirmed"
               ) 

confirmed
# confirmed$date <- as.Date(confirmed$date)

confirmed$date <- mdy(confirmed$date)

Visualize Covid19 Global Confirmed

# covid cases by date
confirmed <- confirmed %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  mutate(confirmed = sum(confirmed))

library(ggplot2)

ggplot(confirmed, aes(x = date, y = confirmed)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(1000000, 2000000, 3000000, 4000000, 5000000), labels = c("1M", "2M", "3M", "4M", "5M")) +
  labs(title = "Covid Confirmed cases (in Millions)", caption = "Source: CSSE at Johns Hopkins University") 

## Function of cases

cases_fun <- function(data, cases) {
  data <- data %>% 
      pivot_longer(cols = 5:ncol(data),
               names_to = "date" , 
               values_to = cases
               ) 
    data$date <- mdy(data$date)
    data
}

# Call function
deaths <- cases_fun(raw_covid19_deaths, "deaths")
confirmed <- cases_fun(raw_covid19_confirmed, "confirmed")
recovered <- cases_fun(raw_covid19_recovered, "recovered")
